## ðŸŽ¯ QUEST 5: The Priority Palace
**Difficulty**: â­â­â­ Hard | **XP**: 300 | **Time**: 30 min

### ðŸ—ºï¸ Mission Briefing
In the Priority Palace, processes compete for the CPU's attention. Master the art of niceness!

### ðŸ‘‘ Royal Court Setup

```bash
cat > ~/linux_adventures/priority_court.sh << 'EOF'
#!/bin/bash

echo "ðŸ‘‘ WELCOME TO THE PRIORITY PALACE ðŸ‘‘"
echo "===================================="
echo ""

# Create nobles of different ranks
echo "Summoning the royal court..."

# The lazy noble (nice = 19, lowest priority)
nice -n 19 bash -c 'echo "ðŸ›Œ Lazy Lord spawned (PID: $$, Nice: 19)"; sleep 200' &
LAZY=$!

# The common noble (nice = 0, default)
nice -n 0 bash -c 'echo "ðŸ§ Common Count spawned (PID: $$, Nice: 0)"; sleep 200' &
COMMON=$!

# Try high priority (needs sudo, will fail for normal users)
nice -n -10 bash -c 'echo "âš¡ Urgent Duke spawned (PID: $$, Nice: -10)"; sleep 200' &
URGENT=$!

echo ""
echo "Court assembled! PIDs: $LAZY, $COMMON, $URGENT"
echo ""
echo "View the hierarchy with:"
echo "ps -o pid,ni,comm -p $LAZY,$COMMON,$URGENT"

# Keep script alive
trap "echo 'Dismissing court...'; kill $LAZY $COMMON $URGENT 2>/dev/null; exit" INT
wait
EOF

chmod +x ~/linux_adventures/priority_court.sh
```

### ðŸ‘‘ Palace Challenges

**Challenge 5.1: The Nice Scale** (60 XP)
```bash
# Start the court
~/linux_adventures/priority_court.sh &
COURT_PID=$!

# View the hierarchy
ps -o pid,ni,comm --ppid $COURT_PID

# CHALLENGE: Which nice values did you see?
# Record them!

# Clean up
kill $COURT_PID
```

**Challenge 5.2: The Promotion Game** (60 XP)
```bash
# Create a peasant process
sleep 500 &
PEASANT=$!

echo "Peasant PID: $PEASANT"

# Check current status
ps -o pid,ni,comm -p $PEASANT

# Promote the peasant (make less nice)
renice -5 $PEASANT

# Verify promotion
ps -o pid,ni,comm -p $PEASANT

# Demote back
renice 10 $PEASANT

# CHALLENGE: What was the final nice value?

kill $PEASANT
```

**Challenge 5.3: CPU Race** (60 XP)
```bash
# Create CPU race script
cat > ~/linux_adventures/cpu_race.sh << 'INNER'
#!/bin/bash

echo "ðŸ CPU RACE STARTING! ðŸ"
echo "======================="

# Racer 1: High priority (low nice)
nice -n -5 bash -c '
    COUNTER=0
    END=$((SECONDS + 10))
    while [ $SECONDS -lt $END ]; do
        ((COUNTER++))
    done
    echo "ðŸŽï¸  Fast Racer counted to: $COUNTER"
' 2>/dev/null &
FAST=$!

# Racer 2: Low priority (high nice)
nice -n 19 bash -c '
    COUNTER=0
    END=$((SECONDS + 10))
    while [ $SECONDS -lt $END ]; do
        ((COUNTER++))
    done
    echo "ðŸŒ Slow Racer counted to: $COUNTER"
' &
SLOW=$!

echo "Racers: Fast ($FAST) vs Slow ($SLOW)"
echo "Racing for 10 seconds..."
echo ""

# Monitor during race
for i in {1..5}; do
    sleep 2
    ps -o pid,ni,%cpu,comm -p $FAST,$SLOW
done

wait

echo ""
echo "Race complete! Who counted higher?"
INNER

chmod +x ~/linux_adventures/cpu_race.sh
~/linux_adventures/cpu_race.sh
```

**Challenge 5.4: The Renice Challenge** (60 XP)
```bash
# Start multiple processes with different priorities
for N in 10 5 0 -5; do
    nice -n $N sleep 600 &
done

# List all with their nice values
ps -eo pid,ni,comm | grep sleep

# CHALLENGE: Adjust ALL sleep processes to nice value 0
# Use a loop!
for PID in $(pgrep sleep); do
    renice 0 $PID
done

# Verify
ps -eo pid,ni,comm | grep sleep

# Cleanup
killall sleep
```

**BOSS CHALLENGE 5.5: Priority Manager Simulator** (60 XP)
```bash
cat > ~/linux_adventures/priority_manager.sh << 'EOF'
#!/bin/bash

echo "ðŸŽ® PRIORITY MANAGER SIMULATOR ðŸŽ®"
echo "================================"
echo ""

# Create various processes
declare -a PIDS
declare -a NAMES

create_process() {
    local name=$1
    local nice=$2
    nice -n $nice sleep 300 &
    PIDS+=($!)
    NAMES+=("$name")
}

echo "Creating processes..."
create_process "WebServer" 0
create_process "Database" -5
create_process "Backup" 15
create_process "Monitor" 10

echo ""
echo "Current Process Status:"
printf "%-15s %-10s %-10s\n" "NAME" "PID" "NICE"
echo "----------------------------------------"

for i in "${!PIDS[@]}"; do
    NICE=$(ps -o ni= -p ${PIDS[$i]})
    printf "%-15s %-10s %-10s\n" "${NAMES[$i]}" "${PIDS[$i]}" "$NICE"
done

echo ""
echo "Your tasks:"
echo "1. Make Backup even lower priority (nice +19)"
echo "2. Give Monitor slightly higher priority (nice 5)"
echo "3. Keep WebServer at default"
echo ""
echo "Commands available:"
echo "  renice <value> <PID>"
echo "  ps -o pid,ni,comm -p <PID>"
echo ""
echo "Press Enter when done to check results..."
read

echo ""
echo "Checking your work..."

# Check if backup is 19
BACKUP_NICE=$(ps -o ni= -p ${PIDS[2]})
if [ "$BACKUP_NICE" -eq 19 ]; then
    echo "âœ… Backup priority: CORRECT"
else
    echo "âŒ Backup priority: INCORRECT (expected 19, got $BACKUP_NICE)"
fi

# Check if monitor is 5
MONITOR_NICE=$(ps -o ni= -p ${PIDS[3]})
if [ "$MONITOR_NICE" -eq 5 ]; then
    echo "âœ… Monitor priority: CORRECT"
else
    echo "âŒ Monitor priority: INCORRECT (expected 5, got $MONITOR_NICE)"
fi

# Cleanup
for PID in "${PIDS[@]}"; do
    kill $PID 2>/dev/null
done

echo ""
echo "Simulation complete!"
EOF

chmod +x ~/linux_adventures/priority_manager.sh
~/linux_adventures/priority_manager.sh
```

