## ðŸŽ¯ QUEST 6: The Zombie Apocalypse
**Difficulty**: â­â­â­â­ Very Hard | **XP**: 400 | **Time**: 40 min

### ðŸ—ºï¸ Mission Briefing
Zombies are harmless... but understanding them makes you a master! Learn the dark art of zombie creation and hunting.

### ðŸ§Ÿ Zombie Lab Setup

```bash
mkdir -p ~/linux_adventures/zombie_lab
cd ~/linux_adventures/zombie_lab

cat > zombie_maker.c << 'EOF'
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <unistd.h>
#include <sys/types.h>

int main() {
    printf("ðŸ§ª ZOMBIE LABORATORY ðŸ§ª\n");
    printf("=====================\n\n");
    
    int zombie_count = 3;
    
    for (int i = 0; i < zombie_count; i++) {
        pid_t pid = fork();
        
        if (pid > 0) {
            // Parent
            printf("Created zombie #%d (PID: %d)\n", i+1, pid);
        } else if (pid == 0) {
            // Child - die immediately
            printf("  Child %d dying...\n", i+1);
            exit(0);
        }
    }
    
    printf("\nZombies created! They will persist for 30 seconds.\n");
    printf("Quick! In another terminal:\n");
    printf("  ps aux | grep defunct\n");
    printf("  ps -eo pid,stat,comm | grep Z\n");
    printf("\nParent PID: %d\n", getpid());
    
    // Parent sleeps, not reaping children
    sleep(30);
    
    printf("\nReaping zombies now...\n");
    // Reap the zombies
    for (int i = 0; i < zombie_count; i++) {
        wait(NULL);
        printf("Zombie #%d reaped\n", i+1);
    }
    
    printf("\nAll zombies eliminated!\n");
    return 0;
}
EOF

# Compile
gcc zombie_maker.c -o zombie_maker 2>/dev/null || echo "Note: gcc needed for this challenge"
```

### ðŸ§Ÿ Zombie Challenges

**Challenge 6.1: Zombie Spotter** (80 XP)
```bash
# Terminal 1: Run zombie maker
~/linux_adventures/zombie_lab/zombie_maker

# Terminal 2: Hunt the zombies!
# Find them quickly before they're reaped!
ps aux | grep defunct

# Alternative method
ps -eo pid,stat,comm | grep '^.* Z'

# CHALLENGE: How many zombies did you find?
# What's their state letter?
```

**Challenge 6.2: Zombie Genealogy** (80 XP)
```bash
# While zombies exist, find their parent
ps -eo pid,ppid,stat,comm | grep defunct

# View the family tree
PARENT_PID=$(ps -eo ppid,stat | grep Z | head -1 | awk '{print $1}')
pstree -p $PARENT_PID

# CHALLENGE: What happens to zombies when parent dies?
```

**Challenge 6.3: Shell Zombie Creator** (80 XP)
```bash
# Create zombies without C!
cat > ~/linux_adventures/zombie_lab/shell_zombies.sh << 'EOF'
#!/bin/bash

echo "ðŸ§Ÿ Creating shell zombies..."

# Method 1: Subshell that exits immediately
(exit) &
ZOMBIE1=$!

# Method 2: Background job that finishes
sleep 0.1 &
ZOMBIE2=$!

echo "Potential zombies created: $ZOMBIE1, $ZOMBIE2"
echo "Parent PID: $$"
echo ""
echo "Check for zombies now:"
echo "  ps -eo pid,ppid,stat,comm | grep $$"

# Keep parent alive
sleep 15

echo ""
echo "Reaping..."
wait
echo "All clean!"
EOF

chmod +x ~/linux_adventures/zombie_lab/shell_zombies.sh
~/linux_adventures/zombie_lab/shell_zombies.sh
```

**Challenge 6.4: Zombie Prevent Defender** (80 XP)
```bash
# The RIGHT way - parent that properly reaps children
cat > ~/linux_adventures/zombie_lab/good_parent.sh << 'EOF'
#!/bin/bash

echo "âœ… RESPONSIBLE PARENT DEMO"
echo "=========================="

# Set up signal handler to reap children
trap 'wait; echo "Child reaped!"' CHLD

echo "Creating child processes..."
for i in {1..5}; do
    (
        echo "Child $i (PID: $$) working..."
        sleep $((RANDOM % 3 + 1))
        echo "Child $i done"
    ) &
done

echo ""
echo "Parent (PID: $$) waiting for children..."
echo "No zombies will be created!"
echo ""

# Check for zombies (should be none)
sleep 2
ZOMBIES=$(ps -eo stat | grep -c Z)
echo "Zombie count: $ZOMBIES"

wait
echo ""
echo "All children properly reaped! âœ¨"
EOF

chmod +x ~/linux_adventures/zombie_lab/good_parent.sh
~/linux_adventures/zombie_lab/good_parent.sh
```

